# Godot Mode — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

Disciplined editing backed by the `godot-grounding` MCP. The loop is **GROUND → EDIT (linted) → CONFIRM**. Work Mode response rules stay in effect (terse).

If the `godot-grounding` tools are unavailable, stop and tell the user to reconnect the MCP server (`/mcp`) before continuing — do not fall back to ungrounded edits.

## When to delegate
For a multi-file change (new subsystem, cross-cutting refactor), hand off to the **godot-editor** subagent with a clear task and file list. For a single-file or small change, run the loop inline.

## Stage 0 — Ground (no guessing)
1. `project_index` to locate the system; `project_find_files` to enumerate files (never glob — it silently misses files here).
2. `project_convention('<topic>')` for the rules that apply.
3. `project_catalog('<kind>')` to confirm valid catalog keys before you use any.
4. `godot_member` / `godot_class` / `godot_search` for the exact signature before any engine call.
5. Read each target file end-to-end before editing.

## Stage 1 — Edit (linted)
- `.gd`: `godot_write_script` (new / full rewrite) or `godot_patch_script` (targeted, exact-match). **Never** raw `Write`/`Edit` on a `.gd` file.
- Optionally `godot_lint_source` the generated code first; fix every lint `error`.
- Writes auto parse-check and roll back on failure — a rollback means fix and retry, never force.

## Stage 2 — Confirm
- `godot_check` each touched script (fast parse/type check, no autoloads).
- For scripts that reference autoloads: `godot_validate` (boots SceneTree so autoloads register).
- `godot_run_tests` filtered to the area (`filter='…'`); full suite for cross-cutting changes. SceneTree validator scripts: `godot_run_script`.
- Report **changes → grounding → test result**. Not done until green.

## Hard rules
- Never raw-write `.gd`; never reference `.godot/imported/`; reference assets by canonical `res://` paths only.
- Strict typing everywhere; past-tense `snake_case` signals (no `on_`); PascalCase `class_name`; ALL_CAPS consts; new folders lowercase.
- `ext_resource` ids are serializer-local — never depend on numeric ids across files.
- Folder renames only via the Godot editor. Do not commit/push — the human gates that.

## Tool reference
| Need | Tool |
|---|---|
| Exact class/method/signal signature | `godot_class` / `godot_member` / `godot_search` |
| Valid catalog keys (effect types, items, …) | `project_catalog` |
| A project convention / rule | `project_convention` |
| Where a system lives | `project_index` |
| Reliable file listing | `project_find_files` |
| References to a symbol (rename safety) | `project_find_refs` |
| Inspect / lint a scene (.tscn) | `project_scene` / `godot_lint_scene` |
| Input actions (project + built-in ui_*) | `project_input_actions` |
| A project setting value | `project_setting` |
| class_name declarations in the project | `project_classes` |
| Named physics/render/nav/avoidance layers | `project_layers` |
| Health-check the setup | `godot_doctor` |
| Lint a file / a snippet | `godot_lint` / `godot_lint_source` |
| Write / patch a `.gd` (linted, rollback) | `godot_write_script` / `godot_patch_script` |
| Parse-check one script | `godot_check` |
| Validate with autoloads (SceneTree boot) | `godot_validate` |
| Run the suite (filtered) | `godot_run_tests` |
| Run a SceneTree/MainLoop script | `godot_run_script` |
| Autofix safe lint issues | `godot_fix_script` |
| Drive the open editor (play/stop/open) | `godot_run_game` / `godot_stop_game` / `godot_open_scene` |
